,"tool_use_result":{"stdout":"/c/repos/Hammer-Forge-Studio/tickets/t4/TICKET-0257.md","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014NXxoLqQ538otULCUFZQWU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TGfw58UEbSswfd13hAkorp","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\tickets\\t4\\TICKET-0257.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":377,"cache_read_input_tokens":29331,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":377},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8aece592-3362-44bf-80b8-4533c2fb5716","uuid":"8b67b9a8-2daa-42f6-9e35-a2b8bf3122cb"},{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TGfw58UEbSswfd13hAkorp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→id: TICKET-0257\n     3→title: \"BUG: status.py does not display effective config values (session_ceiling_usd not visible)\"\n     4→type: BUG\n     5→status: OPEN\n     6→priority: P2\n     7→owner: systems-programmer\n     8→created_by: qa-engineer\n     9→created_at: 2026-03-01\n    10→updated_at: 2026-03-01\n    11→milestone: \"T4\"\n    12→phase: \"Foundation\"\n    13→depends_on: [\"TICKET-0251\"]\n    14→blocks: []\n    15→tags: [orchestrator, status, config, bug, t4-foundation]\n    16→---\n    17→\n    18→## Summary\n    19→\n    20→`status.py` does not display effective configuration values. TICKET-0256 acceptance criterion\n    21→requires that `python orchestrator/status.py --instance M8` shows `session_ceiling_usd: 10`\n    22→when `config.local.json` contains `{\"budgets\": {\"session_ceiling_usd\": 10}}`. The command\n    23→produces no config output, making config layering unverifiable via CLI.\n    24→\n    25→TICKET-0251 implementation notes specified importing `load_config` from `instance_paths`, but\n    26→the merged implementation only imports `resolve_instance` and does not call or display config.\n    27→\n    28→---\n    29→\n    30→## Reproduction Steps\n    31→\n    32→1. Ensure `orchestrator/instances/M8/state.json` exists (run `start_milestone.py M8 --force`)\n    33→2. Create `orchestrator/config.local.json` with content: `{\"budgets\": {\"session_ceiling_usd\": 10}}`\n    34→3. Run: `python orchestrator/status.py --instance M8`\n    35→4. Observe the output\n    36→\n    37→---\n    38→\n    39→## Expected Behavior\n    40→\n    41→The status output should include the effective configuration values, showing:\n    42→- `session_ceiling_usd: 10` (from config.local.json override)\n    43→- All other config values at their defaults from `config.json`\n    44→\n    45→This makes config layering verifiable without requiring a Python REPL session.\n    46→\n    47→---\n    48→\n    49→## Actual Behavior\n    50→\n    51→`status.py` output shows only state values (status, milestone, phase, wave, cost, workers,\n    52→completed waves, retries). No config values are displayed. Sample output:\n    53→\n    54→```\n    55→==================================================\n    56→  Hammer Forge Studio — Orchestrator Status\n    57→==================================================\n    58→\n    59→  Instance:   M8\n    60→  Status:     PLANNING\n    61→  Milestone:  M8\n    62→  Phase:\n    63→  Wave:       0\n    64→  Started:    2026-03-01T21:14:58\n    65→  Total cost: $0.00\n    66→```\n    67→\n    68→---\n    69→\n    70→## Evidence\n    71→\n    72→- Confirmed via: `python orchestrator/status.py --instance M8` — no config section in output\n    73→- Confirmed config layering itself works: `load_config()` returns `session_ceiling_usd: 10`\n    74→  when `config.local.json` is present (verified via direct Python call in TICKET-0256 smoke test)\n    75→- `status.py` source confirms: only `resolve_instance` is imported; `load_config` is never called\n    76→\n    77→---\n    78→\n    79→## Impact\n    80→\n    81→P2 — Defect in expected behavior; workaround exists. The config layering mechanism works\n    82→correctly at the library level. Users can verify the effective config by importing\n    83→`instance_paths.load_config()` directly in Python, but there is no CLI-level visibility.\n    84→\n    85→---\n    86→\n    87→## Suggested Fix\n    88→\n    89→In `status.py`, import `load_config` from `instance_paths` and add a config section to\n    90→`_print_full_status()` that displays the effective merged config (or at least the `budgets`\n    91→section) when not in `--json` mode.\n    92→\n    93→---\n    94→\n    95→## Activity Log\n    96→\n    97→- 2026-03-01 [qa-engineer] Created — filed during TICKET-0256 integration smoke test; config\n    98→  layering display criterion failed against status.py output\n    99→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8aece592-3362-44bf-80b8-4533c2fb5716","uuid":"ed6cf5b8-832f-4b2f-a244-0b0c85456607","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\repos\\Hammer-Forge-Studio\\tickets\\t4\\TICKET-0257.md","content":"---\nid: TICKET-0257\ntitle: \"BUG: status.py does not display effective config values (session_ceiling_usd not visible)\"\ntype: BUG\nstatus: OPEN\npriority: P2\nowner: systems-programmer\ncreated_by: qa-engineer\ncreated_at: 2026-03-01\nupdated_at: 2026-03-01\nmilestone: \"T4\"\nphase: \"Foundation\"\ndepends_on: [\"TICKET-0251\"]\nblocks: []\ntags: [orchestrator, status, config, bug, t4-foundation]\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n`status.py` does not display effective configuration values. TICKET-0256 acceptance criterion\nrequires that `python orchestrator/status.py --instance M8` shows `session_ceiling_usd: 10`\nwhen `config.local.json` contains `{\"budgets\": {\"session_ceiling_usd\": 10}}`. The command\nproduces no config output, making config layering unverifiable via CLI.\n\nTICKET-0251 implementation notes specified importing `load_config` from `instance_paths`, but\nthe merged implementation only imports `resolve_instance` and does not call or display config.\n\n---\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Ensure `orchestrator/instances/M8/state.json` exists (run `start_milestone.py M8 --force`)\n2. Create `orchestrator/config.local.json` with content: `{\"budgets\": {\"session_ceiling_usd\": 10}}`\n3. Run: `python orchestrator/status.py --instance M8`\n4. Observe the output\n\n---\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nThe status output should include the effective configuration values, showing:\n- `session_ceiling_usd: 10` (from config.local.json override)\n- All other config values at their defaults from `config.json`\n\nThis makes config layering verifiable without requiring a Python REPL session.\n\n---\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\n`status.py` output shows only state values (status, milestone, phase, wave, cost, workers,\ncompleted waves, retries). No config values are displayed. Sample output:\n\n```\n==================================================\n  Hammer Forge Studio — Orchestrator Status\n==================================================\n\n  Instance:   M8\n  Status:     PLANNING\n  Milestone:  M8\n  Phase:\n  Wave:       0\n  Started:    2026-03-01T21:14:58\n  Total cost: $0.00\n```\n\n---\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Confirmed via: `python orchestrator/status.py --instance M8` — no config section in output\n- Confirmed config layering itself works: `load_config()` returns `session_ceiling_usd: 10`\n  when `config.local.json` is present (verified via direct Python call in TICKET-0256 smoke test)\n- `status.py` source confirms: only `resolve_instance` is imported; `load_config` is never called\n\n---\n\n## Impact\n\nP2 — Defect in expected behavior; workaround exists. The config layering mechanism works\ncorrectly at the library level. Users can verify the effective config by importing\n`instance_paths.load_config()` directly in Python, but there is no CLI-level visibility.\n\n---\n\n## Suggested Fix\n\nIn `status.py`, import `load_config` from `instance_paths` and add a config section to\n`_print_full_status()` that displays the effective merged config (or at least the `budgets`\nsection) when not in `--json` mode.\n\n---\n\n## Activity Log\n\n- 2026-03-01 [qa-engineer] Created — filed during TICKET-0256 integration smoke test; config\n  layering display criterion failed against status.py output\n","numLines":99,"startLine":1,"totalLines":99}}},{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016tvqBwbZawHYLHxyEZWWy8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me plan the wave:\n\n- TICKET-0257 is OPEN with dependency TICKET-0251 DONE → workable\n- Owner: systems-programmer\n- This is a Python-only fix (status.py in orchestrator/), no game code modification needed\n- needs_worktree: false (modifies /orchestrator/, not /game/)\n- needs_godot_mcp: false\n- budget_usd: 0.50 (it's a P2 bug with a clear suggested fix — simple import + display addition)\n\nThe retry queue had TICKET-0252 but it's already DONE so nothing to retry.\n\n\nThis is the last open ticket in the Foundation phase, so once it's complete the phase gate should trigger. I'll spawn it now and output the JSON.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1369,"cache_read_input_tokens":29708,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1369},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","in